<TextBlock Name="Text003_None" IsManipulationEnabled="False" TextWrapping="Wrap" Margin="0,0,0,20" Width="1018" Height="102" FontFamily="AR CARTER" FontSize="21" Foreground="#FF000000">Notice how gravity (besides being always present, of course!) always points straight down.  Also notice how the normal force is always straight up from the SURFACE.  These two forces often confuse students the most, but if you remember that gravity is straight down and normal force is straight up from the surface, you'll be just fine.<TextBlock.RenderTransform><MatrixTransform><MatrixTransform.Matrix><Matrix OffsetX ="9" OffsetY="475" M11="1" M22="1" /></MatrixTransform.Matrix></MatrixTransform></TextBlock.RenderTransform></TextBlock>
